<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFF6A40FCEF958C1FE8BE98" pageId="4" pageNumber="762" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFF6A40FCEF958C1FE8BE98" blockId="4.[786,1380,902,1330]" lastBlockId="4.[174,1384,1337,3068]" pageId="4" pageNumber="762">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFF6A40FCEF958C1D85B8C4" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[787,901,981,1014]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotoecus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="762" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotoecus</taxonomicName>
was considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFFF6A40FCEE95A41D90BF2C" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1819" box="[786,912,1021,1054]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Nycticeius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="762" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nycticeius</taxonomicName>
by J. R. Ellerman and T. GC. S. Morrison-Scott in 1951 but was subsequently recognized as a distinct genus by D. R. Rosevear in 1965, a treatment followed by J. E. Hill in 1974. Two subspecies have been recognized on the basis of external and skull measurements, but in 2013 M. Happold stated that morphometric differences between the subspecies are slight, although the ranges of the two appear to be well separated by the rainforests of the 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFFF6A40FC4093381A19BEB0" box="[956,1049,1377,1410]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="4" pageNumber="762">Congo</collectingCountry>
Basin. Two subspecies tentatively recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
